her native hue, the grace in every limb, and the delights that her embraces yield.
Besides, the more you strive to part our loves, the more will each of us continue to baffle you, as we have pledged our faith.
You shall not have the credit of this with impunity:
the girl, whose love for me approaches to madness, shall know of it, and she will become your enemy, and no silent one.
