Oh the delight that I have in recalling that night!
how often is its remem­ brance to be appealed to in my prayers !
It was then I saw you, Gallus, dying in the embrace of a maid, and spending long hours of converse with her.
Though sleep was weighing down my wearied eyes, and the moon was blushing in her chariot from the middle of the sky;
yet I could not withdraw from witnessing your sport, so ardent was the affection ex­ pressed in your intercourse.
But since you did not fear to intrust me with your love, accept a token of the pleasure that I received.
