ELTON.HAD he not hands of rare device, whoe'er First painted Love in figure of a boy ?
He saw what thoughtless beings lovers were, Who blessings lose, whilst lightest cares employ.
Nor added he those airy wings in vain, And bade through human hearts the godhead fly;
For we are tost upon a wavering main ;
